WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:00.959 --> 00:00:02.001
<i>I need more dragonriders.</i>

2
00:00:02.002 --> 00:00:04.461
You understand.
to claim a dragon.

3
00:00:04.462 --> 00:00:07.089
<i>you must also
be prepared to die.</i>

4
00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:15.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

5
00:00:16.641 --> 00:00:17.934
<i>It was a reckless thought</i>

6
00:00:18.101 --> 00:00:19.518
that an ancient Valyrian beast

7
00:00:19.519 --> 00:00:21.187
would suffer a
Darklyn to ride it.

8
00:00:21.312 --> 00:00:23.523
Surely it was
not the only possibility.

9
00:00:23.690 --> 00:00:25.149
<i>I'll see my brother.</i>

10
00:00:25.150 --> 00:00:26.692
What do you remember?

11
00:00:27.944 --> 00:00:30.613
I remember nothing.

12
00:00:32.615 --> 00:00:34.815
<i>The small folk of
King's Landing are listening.</i>

13
00:00:34.993 --> 00:00:36.494
<i>They are hungry.</i>

14
00:00:36.703 --> 00:00:38.204
Our gift is sent.

15
00:00:42.709 --> 00:00:44.044
Give it to me!

16
00:00:45.295 --> 00:00:47.046
Your Graces. we must leave.

17
00:00:47.047 --> 00:00:48.380
Let's go.

18
00:00:48.381 --> 00:00:50.050
There's the queen of fishes!

19
00:00:50.175 --> 00:00:52.344
Long live Queen Rhaenyra!

20
00:00:53.720 --> 00:00:56.055
If you have any counsel for
dealing with the river lords.

21
00:00:56.056 --> 00:00:57.181
I'd be glad of it.

22
00:00:57.182 --> 00:00:59.351
But Grover Tully is
their Lord Paramount.

23
00:00:59.684 --> 00:01:02.520
Without him. they will never
raise their banners as one.

24
00:01:03.229 --> 00:01:04.688
This is Ser Oscar Tully.

25
00:01:04.689 --> 00:01:05.898
grandson to Grover Tully.

26
00:01:05.899 --> 00:01:07.067
He is heir to Riverrun

27
00:01:07.233 --> 00:01:09.235
and the future Lord
Paramount of the Riverlands.

28
00:01:09.402 --> 00:01:12.655
<i>Houses Bracken and Blackwood
have long detested one another.</i>

29
00:01:14.532 --> 00:01:16.576
We have fought them
for an age and more.

30
00:01:16.868 --> 00:01:18.327
There are things
the crown itself

31
00:01:18.328 --> 00:01:20.205
must not be seen to do.

32
00:01:20.580 --> 00:01:21.872
Show them your worst.

33
00:01:21.873 --> 00:01:23.667
I am your servant. Your Grace.

34
00:01:24.876 --> 00:01:26.544
<i>There were works of barbarity.</i>

35
00:01:26.878 --> 00:01:30.839
Dragon or no. we shall not
raise our banners for a tyrant.

36
00:01:30.840 --> 00:01:33.426
Your Grace. Lord Grover is dead.

37
00:01:33.760 --> 00:01:35.720
<i>Young Oscar Tully is now</i>

38
00:01:35.929 --> 00:01:37.222
<i>Lord Paramount
of the Riverlands.</i>

39
00:01:37.389 --> 00:01:39.149
When I take King's Landing.

40
00:01:39.265 --> 00:01:40.891
Rhaenyra is welcome
to join me there

41
00:01:40.892 --> 00:01:42.852
and take her place by my side.

42
00:01:45.188 --> 00:01:47.607
There is a large
dragon in the Vale.

43
00:01:47.774 --> 00:01:49.567
Large. but alas wild.

44
00:01:49.693 --> 00:01:51.903
<i>You saved his life. brother.</i>

45
00:01:52.195 --> 00:01:53.915
<i>Do you never think
about what could be ours?</i>

46
00:02:00.745 --> 00:02:02.625
<i>Your Grace. the dragon Seasmoke</i>

47
00:02:02.747 --> 00:02:04.457
has been sighted
flying over Spicetown.

48
00:02:04.582 --> 00:02:06.584
From what we have
heard. he has a rider.

49
00:04:46.411 --> 00:04:52.541
You stand before the
Queen of the Seven Kingdoms...

50
00:04:52.542 --> 00:04:55.754
with a dragon of
House Targaryen!

51
00:04:56.880 --> 00:04:59.214
I had no design upon it!

52
00:04:59.215 --> 00:05:01.259
What do you want?!

53
00:05:02.052 --> 00:05:05.263
To learn
the ways of dragonriders.

54
00:05:06.598 --> 00:05:08.767
And to serve my queen!

55
00:05:10.393 --> 00:05:12.479
Your Grace!

56
00:05:39.756 --> 00:05:41.965
You kneel quickly...

57
00:05:41.966 --> 00:05:44.594
for a man so suddenly elevated.

58
00:05:45.136 --> 00:05:49.140
This dragon came
to me. not I to him.

59
00:05:51.142 --> 00:05:55.355
I have sweated blood in
service of House Velaryon.

60
00:05:55.480 --> 00:05:57.816
I may appear lowborn...

61
00:05:57.941 --> 00:06:00.985
but I know much
and more of service!

62
00:06:02.320 --> 00:06:04.489
And if the gods call
me to greater things.

63
00:06:04.614 --> 00:06:06.324
who am I to refuse them?

64
00:06:16.001 --> 00:06:17.168
Stand.

65
00:06:25.468 --> 00:06:26.969
What is your parentage?

66
00:06:26.970 --> 00:06:29.347
My mother was a shipwright.

67
00:06:30.473 --> 00:06:32.183
My father is...

68
00:06:33.351 --> 00:06:34.686
no one of consequence.

69
00:06:35.311 --> 00:06:38.313
Your ancestors. any
of House Targaryen?

70
00:06:38.314 --> 00:06:41.985
We're not the sort of family
to keep annals. Your Grace.

71
00:06:43.987 --> 00:06:45.697
What is your name?

72
00:06:45.905 --> 00:06:48.324
Addam... of Hull.

73
00:06:56.833 --> 00:06:59.210
You have done something...

74
00:07:00.503 --> 00:07:02.505
I feared impossible...

75
00:07:04.174 --> 00:07:06.176
Addam of Hull.

76
00:07:10.722 --> 00:07:12.724
I am glad of it.

77
00:07:16.853 --> 00:07:19.064
Do you think you can
get him to Dragonstone?

78
00:07:22.067 --> 00:07:23.860
I can try.

79
00:07:29.699 --> 00:07:31.575
All my life...

80
00:07:31.576 --> 00:07:36.081
I have endeavored to serve
both my house and the realm.

81
00:07:37.749 --> 00:07:39.459
And somehow none of it matters.

82
00:07:41.711 --> 00:07:43.588
We are cast aside.

83
00:07:45.590 --> 00:07:47.092
Or hated.

84
00:07:50.053 --> 00:07:52.639
You'll have a scar...

85
00:07:52.764 --> 00:07:55.934
but... it
will be easily hidden.

86
00:08:01.314 --> 00:08:03.149
Nothing is clean here.

87
00:08:12.909 --> 00:08:15.286
I wish to go out. Ser Rickard.

88
00:08:15.662 --> 00:08:17.247
Out?

89
00:08:17.747 --> 00:08:19.165
To the Kingswood. I think.

90
00:08:19.290 --> 00:08:20.667
Then I'll have the
stewards prepare

91
00:08:20.792 --> 00:08:22.794
- a retinue.
- No retinue.

92
00:08:23.795 --> 00:08:25.672
- Then your handmaidens...
- No handmaidens.

93
00:08:25.797 --> 00:08:28.466
Just you.

94
00:08:37.809 --> 00:08:41.770
What are
they for? The block or the crow cage?

95
00:08:41.771 --> 00:08:44.149
The Wall.

96
00:08:44.274 --> 00:08:46.316
The prince regent is merciful.

97
00:08:49.112 --> 00:08:51.780
Well. they started a riot.

98
00:08:51.781 --> 00:08:54.951
Justice is served. I suppose.

99
00:09:02.167 --> 00:09:05.670
I have received word of a
matter of great importance.

100
00:09:06.546 --> 00:09:09.841
Rumor of a sighting of
the dragon Seasmoke...

101
00:09:10.842 --> 00:09:12.552
with a rider.

102
00:09:13.678 --> 00:09:15.637
A fine piece of intelligence.

103
00:09:15.638 --> 00:09:19.392
and now you seek favor by
delivering it to Prince Aemond.

104
00:09:19.517 --> 00:09:23.645
Actually. I thought I might
seek your advice. Lord Larys.

105
00:09:23.646 --> 00:09:25.690
Whispers being your province.

106
00:09:26.149 --> 00:09:29.861
Kneel before the Prince
Regent Aemond Targaryen!

107
00:09:30.320 --> 00:09:32.488
But this is your whisper.

108
00:09:32.489 --> 00:09:35.032
Lord Jasper. not mine.

109
00:09:35.033 --> 00:09:37.911
But if you consider
it valuable...

110
00:09:38.036 --> 00:09:40.080
perhaps you could deliver it

111
00:09:40.205 --> 00:09:42.498
and find favor with
Aemond yourself.

112
00:09:42.499 --> 00:09:45.042
You will
forsake your white cloaks for black.

113
00:09:45.043 --> 00:09:47.878
Serve out your days at The Wall.

114
00:09:47.879 --> 00:09:49.881
Who is this rider?

115
00:09:50.006 --> 00:09:52.883
That is less clear.

116
00:09:52.884 --> 00:09:55.220
but it must surely
be the Lady Rhaena.

117
00:09:55.345 --> 00:09:57.055
She has wanted for
a dragon all her life.

118
00:09:57.180 --> 00:09:58.723
Indeed. but she tried already

119
00:09:58.848 --> 00:09:59.933
when she was four and ten.

120
00:10:00.058 --> 00:10:02.268
The beast Seasmoke
very nearly devoured her.

121
00:10:02.394 --> 00:10:03.603
Who else?

122
00:10:04.938 --> 00:10:07.774
Yes. it is a shallow pool.

123
00:10:07.899 --> 00:10:09.692
Where did you hear it?

124
00:10:09.693 --> 00:10:11.069
My squire.

125
00:10:12.737 --> 00:10:15.072
He heard it from a stablehand.

126
00:10:15.073 --> 00:10:18.701
who heard it from
his father. a fisherman.

127
00:10:18.702 --> 00:10:21.246
whose shipmate claims he saw it.

128
00:10:26.626 --> 00:10:29.086
You are. of course.
welcome to bring this news

129
00:10:29.087 --> 00:10:31.881
to the prince regent. but. um...

130
00:10:32.549 --> 00:10:36.428
perhaps this is one of those
whispers best left to the wind.

131
00:11:16.634 --> 00:11:18.469
The queen is unharmed.

132
00:11:18.470 --> 00:11:21.305
What of the
rider? Do we know who he is?

133
00:11:21.306 --> 00:11:23.141
He appears to be a shipwright

134
00:11:23.266 --> 00:11:25.100
in your employ. Lord Hand.

135
00:11:25.101 --> 00:11:26.602
A commoner?

136
00:11:26.603 --> 00:11:29.189
With respect to your
workers. Lord Corlys.

137
00:11:29.314 --> 00:11:33.275
the lowborn cannot go
around seizing dragons.

138
00:11:33.276 --> 00:11:35.320
Has the thief been secured?

139
00:11:35.445 --> 00:11:38.822
Her Grace has commanded
that he remain here as a guest.

140
00:11:38.823 --> 00:11:40.282
She wishes him to be instructed

141
00:11:40.283 --> 00:11:42.659
in the art of dragonriding.

142
00:11:42.660 --> 00:11:45.830
and that I should teach
him some High Valyrian.

143
00:11:45.955 --> 00:11:47.956
We know nothing about this man.

144
00:11:47.957 --> 00:11:49.792
save that he is lowborn.

145
00:11:49.793 --> 00:11:52.212
What say you. Lord Hand?

146
00:11:53.630 --> 00:11:55.507
We will await the
queen's accounting...

147
00:11:56.383 --> 00:11:59.469
before passing judgment.

148
00:12:01.805 --> 00:12:03.348
Where is the queen?

149
00:12:05.183 --> 00:12:07.686
Her Grace sends word
she will not be attending.

150
00:12:12.023 --> 00:12:14.734
<i>So he serves
you and not himself.</i>

151
00:12:15.026 --> 00:12:17.653
- That is lucky.
- Lucky?

152
00:12:17.654 --> 00:12:19.822
Or somehow ordained?

153
00:12:19.823 --> 00:12:21.490
Seasmoke chose him.

154
00:12:21.491 --> 00:12:24.869
He surely has Targaryen
blood in him somewhere.

155
00:12:24.994 --> 00:12:26.161
The dragon must sense it.

156
00:12:26.162 --> 00:12:27.205
There will be others.

157
00:12:27.330 --> 00:12:28.248
We will find riders

158
00:12:28.373 --> 00:12:29.541
for Vermithor and Silverwing.

159
00:12:29.666 --> 00:12:31.084
You trust this man?

160
00:12:31.876 --> 00:12:33.168
What choice do I have?

161
00:12:33.169 --> 00:12:34.503
He has a dragon.

162
00:12:34.504 --> 00:12:36.171
Without him. I have only Syrax

163
00:12:36.172 --> 00:12:38.550
who may give Aemond
a second thought.

164
00:12:39.092 --> 00:12:41.177
The question is where to look.

165
00:12:41.553 --> 00:12:45.556
Targaryen blood was perhaps
too thin in Ser Steffon Darklyn.

166
00:12:45.557 --> 00:12:48.017
If I can find others
with a more direct line

167
00:12:48.018 --> 00:12:51.062
of breeding.

168
00:12:51.187 --> 00:12:53.273
Forgive me. Your Grace...

169
00:12:55.358 --> 00:12:59.863
but you are better served looking
under the sheets and in the woodpiles.

170
00:13:03.616 --> 00:13:05.534
I once worked in
a pleasure house

171
00:13:05.535 --> 00:13:09.748
where generations of Targaryen
princelings had their revels.

172
00:13:09.873 --> 00:13:13.375
There are four score of
their bastard progeny at least.

173
00:13:13.376 --> 00:13:15.086
that are known to me.

174
00:13:15.211 --> 00:13:17.212
There are sure to be more.

175
00:13:17.213 --> 00:13:19.256
Perhaps some here.
on Dragonstone.

176
00:13:19.257 --> 00:13:23.136
the misbegotten
offspring of your house.

177
00:13:32.812 --> 00:13:34.229
You speak of the lowborn.

178
00:13:34.230 --> 00:13:35.731
They are as like to serve you

179
00:13:35.732 --> 00:13:39.486
as highborn lords or
ladies. perhaps more.

180
00:13:41.654 --> 00:13:44.824
But in the highborn
houses there is...

181
00:13:44.949 --> 00:13:47.619
an ancient fealty.

182
00:13:48.620 --> 00:13:49.788
There is honor.

183
00:13:50.455 --> 00:13:53.749
Your royal half-brothers.
Aegon and Aemond.

184
00:13:53.750 --> 00:13:59.839
whose blood is pure. who wage
war against you for your throne.

185
00:13:59.964 --> 00:14:01.591
are they bound by honor?

186
00:14:07.013 --> 00:14:10.599
A common shipwright
vows to serve you

187
00:14:10.600 --> 00:14:13.853
while your brothers
seek to destroy you.

188
00:14:15.480 --> 00:14:19.651
The order of things has
changed. Your Grace.

189
00:14:20.360 --> 00:14:22.487
Why not embrace it?

190
00:14:31.955 --> 00:14:35.041
For 20 years. the lords
of this realm levied...

191
00:14:35.166 --> 00:14:38.837
insults at my sons
behind my back.

192
00:14:46.344 --> 00:14:47.679
Well then.

193
00:14:48.680 --> 00:14:52.475
Let us raise an
army of bastards.

194
00:15:13.038 --> 00:15:15.707
- My lord.
- "My lord"?

195
00:15:16.207 --> 00:15:18.543
How you have
come up in the world.

196
00:15:20.712 --> 00:15:22.880
I wish to ask for leave
to relinquish my part

197
00:15:22.881 --> 00:15:24.840
as a shipwright in your service.

198
00:15:24.841 --> 00:15:27.886
There are good men and
strong who can take my place...

199
00:15:32.891 --> 00:15:35.060
Your leave is granted.

200
00:15:47.072 --> 00:15:48.573
Well done.

201
00:16:16.893 --> 00:16:19.395
Lord Tully has
answered your summons and brought

202
00:16:19.396 --> 00:16:21.981
the Riverlords. my king.

203
00:16:27.070 --> 00:16:30.072
My condolences
on the passing of your grandsire

204
00:16:30.073 --> 00:16:33.118
but the crown congratulates you on
your ascension to the head of your house

205
00:16:33.243 --> 00:16:34.952
and Lord Paramount
in the Riverlands.

206
00:16:34.953 --> 00:16:36.287
Truly glorious. Well done.

207
00:16:37.247 --> 00:16:41.750
- I did nothing.
- Nevertheless. you are here. which is the important thing.

208
00:16:41.751 --> 00:16:43.585
You were quick enough
to dismiss me before.

209
00:16:43.586 --> 00:16:46.130
You were of no
significance to me then.

210
00:16:46.131 --> 00:16:47.590
Now...

211
00:16:50.135 --> 00:16:52.762
I shall have my great host.

212
00:16:53.513 --> 00:16:55.806
You have a decision to make.

213
00:16:55.807 --> 00:16:58.143
I presume it is clear to
you which is the right one.

214
00:16:58.977 --> 00:17:00.769
You'll forgive me. Your Grace.

215
00:17:00.770 --> 00:17:02.855
I am green in
this sort of matter.

216
00:17:02.856 --> 00:17:06.818
as you so kindly point
out. but...

217
00:17:07.777 --> 00:17:11.280
it does seem to me that
you've made rather a mess here.

218
00:17:11.281 --> 00:17:15.284
countenancing barbarities
in the queen's name.

219
00:17:15.285 --> 00:17:17.537
Whose side are you on?

220
00:17:21.833 --> 00:17:25.003
The Riverlands are
held together by oaths.

221
00:17:26.546 --> 00:17:30.508
House Tully swore
an oath to King Viserys.

222
00:17:32.135 --> 00:17:33.386
We recognize the authority

223
00:17:33.511 --> 00:17:36.014
of the named heir.
Queen Rhaenyra

224
00:17:36.473 --> 00:17:40.352
and your own...
as her king consort.

225
00:17:41.686 --> 00:17:42.854
Good.

226
00:17:43.980 --> 00:17:45.481
Then we shall go
to face your vassals

227
00:17:45.482 --> 00:17:46.815
and you will call
your banners to war.

228
00:17:46.816 --> 00:17:49.486
That might be
difficult. my king.

229
00:17:54.366 --> 00:17:55.700
Well...

230
00:17:56.910 --> 00:17:58.494
I was told they
would come to heel

231
00:17:58.495 --> 00:18:00.996
when House Tully
declared its allegiance.

232
00:18:00.997 --> 00:18:02.998
That may be the case.

233
00:18:02.999 --> 00:18:06.001
though it is yet to be seen
that they will heed my authority

234
00:18:06.002 --> 00:18:08.046
as young as it is.

235
00:18:09.547 --> 00:18:11.716
And there is another problem.

236
00:18:13.551 --> 00:18:15.344
They all hate you.

237
00:18:18.682 --> 00:18:20.558
I don't need their love.

238
00:18:20.684 --> 00:18:22.851
I need their swords.

239
00:18:25.271 --> 00:18:29.234
Your Grace. my lord.
The Riverlords await.

240
00:18:29.359 --> 00:18:31.861
I fear we cannot
delay them any longer.

241
00:18:38.410 --> 00:18:40.745
Come along. Lord Oscar.

242
00:19:03.101 --> 00:19:05.770
In the deepest darkness
comes the dawn.

243
00:19:06.396 --> 00:19:07.772
A new lord.

244
00:19:07.897 --> 00:19:09.607
a new beginning.

245
00:19:10.567 --> 00:19:13.153
Let us put all the old
unpleasantness behind us.

246
00:19:19.284 --> 00:19:21.286
Be welcome. my lords...

247
00:19:22.162 --> 00:19:25.414
and you have my thanks
for answering my summons.

248
00:19:25.415 --> 00:19:27.959
I know I'm not the
man my grandsire was.

249
00:19:28.084 --> 00:19:32.921
but I hope to begin well.
and go on from there.

250
00:19:32.922 --> 00:19:36.176
Well said.
One thing is clear...

251
00:19:36.801 --> 00:19:40.095
the Rivermen honor the old
ways and abide by tradition.

252
00:19:40.096 --> 00:19:42.097
Here. then. is tradition.

253
00:19:42.098 --> 00:19:43.516
Grover Tully is dead.

254
00:19:43.641 --> 00:19:45.477
Lord Oscar raised
up in his place.

255
00:19:45.602 --> 00:19:47.187
You have been summoned here

256
00:19:47.312 --> 00:19:48.937
to swear anew
your fealty to him.

257
00:19:48.938 --> 00:19:53.108
and as his bannermen.
answer his call.

258
00:19:53.109 --> 00:19:55.152
And what would that call be?

259
00:19:55.153 --> 00:19:57.364
In his wisdom. he
has pledged his house.

260
00:19:57.489 --> 00:19:59.281
and yours. to me.

261
00:20:01.117 --> 00:20:04.495
Lord Oscar. for
generations we have been guided

262
00:20:04.496 --> 00:20:06.623
by the judgment
of your forebears.

263
00:20:06.956 --> 00:20:10.459
Why should we now follow a
boy. younger than my own sons.

264
00:20:10.460 --> 00:20:11.794
when you will align with one

265
00:20:11.795 --> 00:20:14.171
who will desecrate the
innocent to reach his aims?

266
00:20:15.674 --> 00:20:19.843
I did only what was
necessary. my lord.

267
00:20:19.844 --> 00:20:22.179
And I now deliver
to you the traitor

268
00:20:22.180 --> 00:20:24.306
Amos Bracken and his son.

269
00:20:24.307 --> 00:20:27.811
No more traitor to his land
than you. Willem Blackwood.

270
00:20:28.520 --> 00:20:30.855
I take to heart your
words. Lord Piper.

271
00:20:30.980 --> 00:20:34.192
and I agree. I-I-I am young.

272
00:20:37.028 --> 00:20:40.240
And I have no love
for Daemon Targaryen.

273
00:20:40.365 --> 00:20:43.702
He has dishonored himself
and the crown with his...

274
00:20:44.577 --> 00:20:47.329
comportment here.

275
00:20:47.330 --> 00:20:51.333
Nevertheless. having so
little experience to guide me.

276
00:20:51.334 --> 00:20:55.170
my best course is to defer to
the oath my grandsire swore

277
00:20:55.171 --> 00:20:59.217
to King Viserys when he
named Rhaenyra his heir.

278
00:21:02.387 --> 00:21:05.848
I see no reason
to cast aside loyalty

279
00:21:05.849 --> 00:21:09.518
no matter how loathsome I may
find her representative the prince.

280
00:21:09.519 --> 00:21:10.937
King.

281
00:21:11.730 --> 00:21:13.898
Mind your tongue. boy.

282
00:21:25.702 --> 00:21:28.204
Will you have our army or not?

283
00:21:38.715 --> 00:21:41.383
I am. in the end. a Riverman

284
00:21:41.384 --> 00:21:43.552
and the word of my house stands.

285
00:21:43.553 --> 00:21:46.388
even if certain people
are unworthy of it.

286
00:21:54.272 --> 00:21:56.775
Your Lord Oscar is bold.

287
00:21:57.942 --> 00:22:00.445
But he is perhaps not wrong.

288
00:22:01.237 --> 00:22:04.073
I may have been a
touch enthusiastic

289
00:22:04.074 --> 00:22:06.909
in pursuing my aims.

290
00:22:06.910 --> 00:22:10.412
But don't allow
my failings to...

291
00:22:10.413 --> 00:22:13.415
keep you from
supporting an upright man.

292
00:22:13.416 --> 00:22:16.336
Lord Oscar.
we honor the old ways.

293
00:22:16.461 --> 00:22:18.797
as Prince Daemon says

294
00:22:18.922 --> 00:22:22.300
- and the old ways call for justice to be done.
- Yes!

295
00:22:22.425 --> 00:22:24.468
Justice has been done.

296
00:22:24.469 --> 00:22:29.140
They who bent the knee to the
usurper have been brought to heel.

297
00:22:29.808 --> 00:22:34.354
And now. we unite
before our liege lord...

298
00:22:36.272 --> 00:22:38.483
and our king consort.

299
00:22:52.372 --> 00:22:56.334
I accept you as my
vassal. Willem Blackwood...

300
00:23:03.466 --> 00:23:04.718
but...

301
00:23:06.052 --> 00:23:09.472
I am Lord Paramount
of all River Houses.

302
00:23:11.182 --> 00:23:12.862
And there is only one
answer for the crimes

303
00:23:12.976 --> 00:23:14.853
you visited upon your neighbors.

304
00:23:18.565 --> 00:23:22.818
I did only what His Grace
the king required of me.

305
00:23:22.819 --> 00:23:26.155
It is true that he
made clear his base desires.

306
00:23:26.156 --> 00:23:29.826
but you did not have to
pursue such savagery.

307
00:23:30.827 --> 00:23:34.706
You did it... because
you wanted to.

308
00:23:34.914 --> 00:23:37.375
Our young lord speaks truly.

309
00:23:39.002 --> 00:23:41.546
Seize him.

310
00:23:42.380 --> 00:23:46.008
Don't fuckin' do this.

311
00:23:46.009 --> 00:23:49.220
Your Grace. command
them. I've only served you.

312
00:23:53.892 --> 00:23:55.851
- Command them.
- If His Grace wishes

313
00:23:55.852 --> 00:23:58.229
to show contrition for his acts

314
00:23:58.355 --> 00:24:02.067
and to prove himself
deserving of our banners

315
00:24:02.859 --> 00:24:05.527
he must now rectify
his grievous error.

316
00:24:05.528 --> 00:24:08.073
Denounce your crimes...

317
00:24:09.366 --> 00:24:12.077
and dispense justice.

318
00:24:13.453 --> 00:24:14.536
Dear.

319
00:24:27.717 --> 00:24:29.719
No. no. no!

320
00:24:30.095 --> 00:24:33.263
I did as you asked. Your
Grace. I have been faithful.

321
00:25:52.677 --> 00:25:54.888
What is this?

322
00:25:56.639 --> 00:25:59.017
I never wanted it.

323
00:26:01.519 --> 00:26:03.855
I was right not to.

324
00:26:07.525 --> 00:26:10.236
All that pain it caused.

325
00:26:13.823 --> 00:26:17.202
It crushes whoever wears it.

326
00:26:20.997 --> 00:26:23.708
You always wanted it. Daemon.

327
00:26:29.047 --> 00:26:31.591
Do you want it still?

328
00:26:40.892 --> 00:26:44.062
- Grand
Maester Orwyle: Steady. Slowly.

329
00:26:47.065 --> 00:26:48.274
I can't.

330
00:26:48.400 --> 00:26:51.236
You can. You
must try. Your Grace.

331
00:26:59.703 --> 00:27:01.870
I can't. I can't!

332
00:27:06.459 --> 00:27:08.586
I'm sorry. Your Grace.
I'm sorry. Your Grace.

333
00:27:08.712 --> 00:27:12.132
God. God.

334
00:27:12.257 --> 00:27:13.382
A moment!

335
00:27:13.383 --> 00:27:16.261
A moment. please!

336
00:27:19.764 --> 00:27:23.476
You really oughtn't to be
doing that alone. Grand Maester.

337
00:27:31.276 --> 00:27:32.568
Allow me.

338
00:27:35.238 --> 00:27:36.781
No. no. no. no. no. no. no.

339
00:27:37.240 --> 00:27:39.117
Forgive me. Your Grace.

340
00:27:50.462 --> 00:27:52.921
- Be careful.
- Wait. wait.

341
00:28:03.683 --> 00:28:06.102
Your progress is impressive.

342
00:28:07.520 --> 00:28:11.608
But I'm afraid you
must work harder.

343
00:28:12.984 --> 00:28:14.986
Your strength will return.

344
00:28:15.111 --> 00:28:17.279
There are... adjustments

345
00:28:17.280 --> 00:28:18.990
to the gait and so forth

346
00:28:19.115 --> 00:28:21.826
that you will learn
now that you are...

347
00:28:22.869 --> 00:28:24.037
as you are.

348
00:28:37.217 --> 00:28:39.469
You should be more cautious.

349
00:28:39.844 --> 00:28:42.137
I. I should. Lord Larys.

350
00:28:42.138 --> 00:28:44.724
He-He needs rest.
He should be abed.

351
00:28:44.849 --> 00:28:47.142
I push him on your instruction.

352
00:28:47.143 --> 00:28:49.521
I'll have the sentry
give you more warning.

353
00:28:52.023 --> 00:28:53.691
Let him try again
in a few hours.

354
00:28:53.692 --> 00:28:55.360
He is spent.

355
00:28:58.363 --> 00:29:01.157
It will be long
before he may rest again.

356
00:29:13.545 --> 00:29:14.713
Alyn.

357
00:29:17.841 --> 00:29:19.384
My lord.

358
00:29:22.387 --> 00:29:25.098
I have tasks that
need your personal attention.

359
00:29:25.515 --> 00:29:28.226
The queen requires ships at
her service in King's Landing.

360
00:29:28.351 --> 00:29:31.061
Charter fishing vessels.
Pay whatever they demand

361
00:29:31.062 --> 00:29:34.357
but ensure their
captains are dependable.

362
00:29:36.526 --> 00:29:38.945
- Put trusted swords aboard.
- Yes. m'lord.

363
00:29:39.070 --> 00:29:40.590
Have them wait just
outside the harbor.

364
00:29:40.697 --> 00:29:43.742
And there will be a message
to carry to one she will name.

365
00:29:50.582 --> 00:29:54.919
The queen has found a new
rider for one of her dragons.

366
00:29:55.420 --> 00:29:57.922
I've heard tell of it.

367
00:29:58.048 --> 00:29:59.424
The rider is your brother.

368
00:30:03.928 --> 00:30:06.431
She now makes
the call for others.

369
00:30:06.931 --> 00:30:09.099
Our people are of Old Valyria.

370
00:30:09.100 --> 00:30:12.729
but... we are no dragonlords.

371
00:30:14.272 --> 00:30:19.444
I confess. I knew little
of your mother's heritage.

372
00:30:21.821 --> 00:30:23.448
If it is...

373
00:30:24.449 --> 00:30:26.618
something in the blood.

374
00:30:31.331 --> 00:30:33.916
My brother was ever restless.

375
00:30:33.917 --> 00:30:36.670
yearning for some
sign of his worth.

376
00:30:38.004 --> 00:30:41.007
I am of salt and sea.

377
00:30:41.132 --> 00:30:43.468
I yearn for nothing else.

378
00:32:44.589 --> 00:32:46.966
I will retire now. Ser Rickard.

379
00:32:54.265 --> 00:32:57.769
When does Your Grace
mean to return to the city?

380
00:32:59.479 --> 00:33:01.731
I'm not yet certain I do.

381
00:33:03.274 --> 00:33:04.567
Good night.

382
00:33:12.826 --> 00:33:16.078
The lowborn claiming dragons.

383
00:33:16.079 --> 00:33:17.913
was it her idea?

384
00:33:17.914 --> 00:33:19.666
Lady Mysaria?

385
00:33:19.791 --> 00:33:22.918
You were enthusiastic enough
when Ser Steffon made his claim.

386
00:33:22.919 --> 00:33:25.254
He was the Lord Commander
of your Queensguard.

387
00:33:25.255 --> 00:33:27.798
Heir to the Dun Fort.
These people are...

388
00:33:27.799 --> 00:33:29.009
Courageous.

389
00:33:29.801 --> 00:33:31.469
Mongrels.

390
00:33:36.975 --> 00:33:38.351
Jace.

391
00:33:41.146 --> 00:33:43.105
Think what is at stake.

392
00:33:43.106 --> 00:33:46.317
I know well what is at stake.

393
00:33:47.986 --> 00:33:50.654
House Targaryen is
the blood of the dragon.

394
00:33:50.655 --> 00:33:53.450
If any may lay claim
to it. what are we then?

395
00:33:53.867 --> 00:33:56.828
The rightful rulers of
the Seven Kingdoms.

396
00:33:57.162 --> 00:34:00.832
And what if one of your
baseborn. silver-haired dragonriders

397
00:34:00.957 --> 00:34:03.668
decides he wants to
rule the Seven Kingdoms?

398
00:34:03.793 --> 00:34:07.213
Did the Conqueror's
dream foretell that?

399
00:34:07.339 --> 00:34:10.008
What else would you have me do?

400
00:34:11.718 --> 00:34:13.553
Prosecute a war.
which we will lose.

401
00:34:13.678 --> 00:34:16.305
in which thousands will die.

402
00:34:16.306 --> 00:34:18.307
Or fly against Vhagar myself?

403
00:34:18.308 --> 00:34:21.895
Or perhaps you will fly
against her on Vermax.

404
00:34:24.481 --> 00:34:29.194
Jace. with these riders.
we can end a needless war.

405
00:34:30.195 --> 00:34:32.697
I may take my rightful
place on my father's throne.

406
00:34:32.822 --> 00:34:34.866
And when you die?

407
00:34:38.703 --> 00:34:41.081
You are my heir.

408
00:34:54.844 --> 00:34:57.555
Did you think I
would have dark hair?

409
00:35:05.522 --> 00:35:07.774
When you took Harwin
Strong into your bed.

410
00:35:07.899 --> 00:35:09.275
did you think I might favor him.

411
00:35:09.401 --> 00:35:10.944
or did it not cross your mind?

412
00:35:13.530 --> 00:35:16.741
- Jacaerys...
- I'm no fool. Mother!

413
00:35:17.242 --> 00:35:19.577
The proof is
here for all to see.

414
00:35:22.080 --> 00:35:24.373
Yet I may argue my
legitimacy to succeed you

415
00:35:24.374 --> 00:35:26.626
because I have a dragon.

416
00:35:29.713 --> 00:35:32.090
And now you say you
will strip that from me too.

417
00:35:48.273 --> 00:35:50.942
I mislike all of this.

418
00:35:52.944 --> 00:35:54.904
Then don't pursue it.

419
00:36:02.912 --> 00:36:06.666
But I cannot gainsay
that which the gods

420
00:36:06.791 --> 00:36:08.585
have laid before me.

421
00:36:33.693 --> 00:36:37.113
Do whatever you must
to see that it finds her.

422
00:37:03.306 --> 00:37:05.016
From the queen.

423
00:37:51.771 --> 00:37:53.440
You won't believe this.

424
00:37:55.358 --> 00:37:57.192
Word is. Rhaenyra's recruiting

425
00:37:57.193 --> 00:37:59.069
smallfolk to go to Dragonstone.

426
00:37:59.070 --> 00:38:02.031
- Fuck that.
- They wouldn't take you anyway.

427
00:38:04.200 --> 00:38:07.704
They're looking... for
Targaryen bastards.

428
00:38:08.580 --> 00:38:10.539
Boats leave tonight.
Hour of the bat.

429
00:38:10.540 --> 00:38:13.793
Seven hells. Ulf.
This is it!

430
00:38:13.918 --> 00:38:15.753
Yeah. a likely story.

431
00:38:15.754 --> 00:38:17.880
- You've been taken in. lads.
- No. no. no. no. no.

432
00:38:17.881 --> 00:38:20.716
The queen's own handmaid
is here. spreadin' the word.

433
00:38:20.717 --> 00:38:22.138
Well. that's a shame
'cause I'd have been

434
00:38:22.218 --> 00:38:25.054
first in line if it
wasn't for my injury.

435
00:38:25.055 --> 00:38:27.185
- 'Cause my leg hasn't been the same since...
- Are you touched?

436
00:38:27.265 --> 00:38:29.224
He's saying you
can claim a dragon.

437
00:38:29.225 --> 00:38:31.770
The barkeep from the
Seven Maesters is goin'.

438
00:38:31.895 --> 00:38:33.313
And two of the
girls from Mother's.

439
00:38:33.438 --> 00:38:36.398
- A chance to stick it to Aemond.
- And claim a dragon.

440
00:38:36.399 --> 00:38:38.567
- Dragon!
- Yeah. no. I know.

441
00:38:38.568 --> 00:38:41.904
- What?
- I know. I just... I can't...

442
00:38:41.905 --> 00:38:44.407
I can't be sure it's all true.

443
00:38:47.786 --> 00:38:51.080
You can't mean that
you've been drinkin'

444
00:38:51.081 --> 00:38:53.582
at the expense of all
these. these good people

445
00:38:53.583 --> 00:38:55.669
- for a fiction? No. Ulf.
- No. no. Shh.

446
00:38:55.794 --> 00:38:57.419
All spark and no tinder?

447
00:38:57.420 --> 00:38:59.175
- They won't be happy.
- They'll be very unhappy.

448
00:38:59.255 --> 00:39:01.298
- Never live it down.
- Never live it down.

449
00:39:01.299 --> 00:39:03.801
- Come on. Ulf. the time has come!
- Come on!

450
00:39:03.802 --> 00:39:05.260
Can I see a little glimmer?

451
00:39:05.261 --> 00:39:07.806
- Where is it?
- There's the Ulf I know.

452
00:39:07.931 --> 00:39:09.973
Yes! Yes. there he is!

453
00:39:09.974 --> 00:39:13.687
- Yes. yes!
- Wine! Wine for Ulf the Dragonlord!

454
00:39:13.812 --> 00:39:15.938
Ulf the Dragonlord!

455
00:39:15.939 --> 00:39:19.775
Ulf the Dragonlord!
Ulf the Dragonlord!

456
00:39:30.995 --> 00:39:33.540
I don't want you to go.

457
00:39:33.665 --> 00:39:35.457
I have to. Kat.

458
00:39:35.458 --> 00:39:37.126
We'll go to my
brother in Tumbleton.

459
00:39:37.127 --> 00:39:39.671
They'll have food.
You'll find work.

460
00:39:39.796 --> 00:39:41.548
I can't ignore this.

461
00:39:45.969 --> 00:39:47.846
I never knew my father.

462
00:39:50.223 --> 00:39:52.225
That much is true.

463
00:39:56.521 --> 00:39:58.690
But I did know my mother.

464
00:40:11.202 --> 00:40:13.704
I hid it from you.

465
00:40:13.705 --> 00:40:15.999
And I'm sorry for that.

466
00:40:19.711 --> 00:40:21.421
She worked...

467
00:40:22.714 --> 00:40:24.049
in a pleasure house.

468
00:40:25.383 --> 00:40:28.261
She was granted
more freedom than most

469
00:40:28.386 --> 00:40:30.889
because of who she was.

470
00:40:33.224 --> 00:40:36.436
And because rich men paid more
to fuck a woman with silver hair.

471
00:40:40.899 --> 00:40:43.026
She used to tell me...

472
00:40:44.069 --> 00:40:47.405
I was no different
to her brother's boys

473
00:40:49.574 --> 00:40:52.744
Viserys... and Daemon.

474
00:40:58.416 --> 00:41:00.418
But I was ashamed of her.

475
00:41:03.254 --> 00:41:06.466
I tried to make my
way with my own hands.

476
00:41:11.054 --> 00:41:13.431
I could not protect you.

477
00:41:14.057 --> 00:41:17.143
I could not keep our girl alive.

478
00:41:24.734 --> 00:41:26.111
And now...

479
00:41:27.779 --> 00:41:31.407
we would never want again.

480
00:41:31.408 --> 00:41:33.952
If I claimed a dragon...

481
00:41:35.078 --> 00:41:37.246
they'd make you a lady.

482
00:41:42.752 --> 00:41:45.463
I do not care to
be a lady. Hugh.

483
00:41:48.174 --> 00:41:50.969
And neither do I
want to be a widow.

484
00:41:58.476 --> 00:42:01.021
I have to do somethin'.

485
00:46:01.052 --> 00:46:05.432
I used to think I knew what it
was to claim a dragon. but...

486
00:46:09.894 --> 00:46:12.564
I understand now that
what I thought I knew is...

487
00:46:13.231 --> 00:46:15.233
ash in the wind.

488
00:46:27.620 --> 00:46:29.913
Perhaps it is blood.

489
00:46:29.914 --> 00:46:32.249
Or worth.

490
00:46:32.250 --> 00:46:34.711
Or perhaps it's something else.

491
00:46:39.049 --> 00:46:45.138
Each of you... has left
behind a life to answer this call.

492
00:46:46.264 --> 00:46:51.269
A life to which... you
might never return.

493
00:46:53.104 --> 00:46:56.274
If you survive. you
will be transformed.

494
00:46:57.317 --> 00:47:01.404
No man or woman can face
a dragon and be otherwise.

495
00:47:06.785 --> 00:47:10.412
Some of you may welcome
the prospect of change.

496
00:47:10.413 --> 00:47:14.167
even death. given
the alternatives:

497
00:47:14.501 --> 00:47:18.922
privation... starvation. war.

498
00:47:19.923 --> 00:47:22.257
This is our purpose.

499
00:47:22.258 --> 00:47:24.636
to end those hardships.

500
00:47:26.513 --> 00:47:27.847
For you...

501
00:47:29.307 --> 00:47:32.686
for your kin. for all the realm.

502
00:47:33.687 --> 00:47:38.024
With these two dragons
added to our number.

503
00:47:38.149 --> 00:47:40.819
the enemy will have no
choice but to give way.

504
00:47:42.195 --> 00:47:44.948
And peace will be restored...

505
00:47:47.200 --> 00:47:50.953
suffering will be ended.

506
00:47:50.954 --> 00:47:53.665
and without bloodshed...

507
00:47:54.833 --> 00:47:56.835
gods willing.

508
00:48:11.725 --> 00:48:13.893
The dragon

509
00:48:14.019 --> 00:48:16.021
named Vermithor...

510
00:48:17.480 --> 00:48:21.025
is the largest in the
world after Vhagar.

511
00:48:21.026 --> 00:48:24.821
and... perhaps. the most fierce.

512
00:48:29.034 --> 00:48:31.160
He's called the Bronze Fury.

513
00:48:37.334 --> 00:48:39.044
We'll go to him now.

514
00:48:41.171 --> 00:48:42.547
And...

515
00:48:45.925 --> 00:48:47.677
may the gods bless you.

516
00:51:49.776 --> 00:51:52.070
Who among you would be first?

517
00:52:21.766 --> 00:52:23.767
I have nothing more to tell you.

518
00:52:23.768 --> 00:52:26.604
It must be the
dragon who speaks.

519
00:54:00.865 --> 00:54:03.535
- Your Grace. we must away!
- No.

520
00:54:39.237 --> 00:54:41.239
Help me! Help...

521
00:54:41.948 --> 00:54:43.116
Help me!

522
00:55:30.622 --> 00:55:31.956
F...

523
00:56:10.829 --> 00:56:12.788
- No!
- Shh. shh. shh!

524
00:57:12.849 --> 00:57:16.060
Here! Here I am!

525
00:57:28.740 --> 00:57:30.240
I'm ready.

526
00:57:45.757 --> 00:57:49.426
Come on!

527
01:01:34.986 --> 01:01:39.281
"Lord Ormund Hightower
makes slow progress.

528
01:01:39.282 --> 01:01:41.784
"There is great
concern that his host

529
01:01:41.785 --> 01:01:42.951
"is threatened on two fronts

530
01:01:42.952 --> 01:01:46.497
by armies allied with
House Beesbury."

531
01:01:48.958 --> 01:01:51.211
However. in happier tidings.

532
01:01:51.336 --> 01:01:52.961
Prince Daeron's
dragon. Tessarion.

533
01:01:52.962 --> 01:01:54.630
has at last taken to wing.

534
01:01:54.631 --> 01:01:57.175
Your brother expects
to join the fight soon.

535
01:01:57.300 --> 01:01:59.511
Dragon!

536
01:01:59.803 --> 01:02:01.221
And when he does.

537
01:02:01.346 --> 01:02:03.972
the Hightower host
will be unstoppable.

538
01:02:03.973 --> 01:02:07.017
Dragon! Inside! Now!

539
01:02:21.366 --> 01:02:23.492
Take positions!

540
01:03:02.198 --> 01:03:03.908
Open the gates!

541
01:05:58.208 --> 01:05:59.709
<i>The dragons dance.</i>

542
01:06:01.252 --> 01:06:03.546
<i>and men are like
dust under their feet.</i>

543
01:06:05.215 --> 01:06:07.216
We march now
toward our annihilation.

544
01:06:10.804 --> 01:06:13.890
<i>I have entrusted
you with a power only few have known.</i>

545
01:06:15.225 --> 01:06:17.811
We must strike while
we have the advantage.

546
01:06:18.478 --> 01:06:20.229
The Prince Regent is angry.

547
01:06:20.230 --> 01:06:21.731
There is no telling
what he will do.

548
01:06:21.981 --> 01:06:23.941
You
wish to rule the Seven Kingdoms.

549
01:06:23.942 --> 01:06:25.902
but you reign ruin and death.

550
01:06:26.778 --> 01:06:28.862
<i>While you have mustered an army.</i>

551
01:06:28.863 --> 01:06:30.073
<i>Rhaenyra has faltered.</i>

552
01:06:30.740 --> 01:06:32.784
Pretenders raise
new riders against us.

553
01:06:32.909 --> 01:06:34.828
I need you to fly with
Dreamfyre to battle.

554
01:06:35.745 --> 01:06:38.456
<i>We will answer
outrage with outrage.</i>

555
01:06:39.916 --> 01:06:42.002
<i>For every one of us who falls.</i>

556
01:06:43.253 --> 01:06:44.921
<i>a hundred of them.</i>

557
01:06:45.171 --> 01:06:47.840
<i>There will be no mercy!</i>

558
01:07:04.149 --> 01:07:06.151
<i>In this
episode. Rhaenyra throws off</i>

559
01:07:06.276 --> 01:07:08.777
<i>all dissenting
opinions around her.</i>

560
01:07:08.778 --> 01:07:10.487
and then takes her
court of commoners

561
01:07:10.488 --> 01:07:12.157
all out onto the platform.

562
01:07:12.657 --> 01:07:14.451
Who among you would be first?

563
01:07:21.958 --> 01:07:23.755
<i>I always talked
about that coastline scene</i>

564
01:07:23.835 --> 01:07:24.961
<i>as a Western showdown.</i>

565
01:07:25.211 --> 01:07:28.048
<i>a scene out of Sergio Leone.</i>
Once Upon a Time in the West...

566
01:07:30.008 --> 01:07:31.967
<i>with the dragon being
the Colt on their hip.</i>

567
01:07:31.968 --> 01:07:33.845
<i>and the way they carefully
approach each other</i>

568
01:07:33.970 --> 01:07:35.347
<i>and size each other up.</i>

569
01:07:35.513 --> 01:07:36.848
What do you want?

570
01:07:37.015 --> 01:07:39.016
<i>Until this point.
she's thinking about people</i>

571
01:07:39.017 --> 01:07:41.394
<i>that are after their own
rise and personal gain.</i>

572
01:07:41.519 --> 01:07:43.233
And I think she wants
to get a sense of whether

573
01:07:43.313 --> 01:07:46.358
she has to kill this
man or kill his dragon.

574
01:07:46.483 --> 01:07:47.901
To serve my Queen.

575
01:07:48.026 --> 01:07:50.861
To meet somebody that
actually does this miraculous thing

576
01:07:50.862 --> 01:07:52.821
and then immediately
bends the knee to her.

577
01:07:52.822 --> 01:07:54.532
<i>in a way. that is
a bit of a shock.</i>

578
01:07:55.033 --> 01:07:57.035
Do you think you can
get him to Dragonstone?

579
01:07:57.160 --> 01:07:59.828
<i>The moment
Addam claims Seasmoke.</i>

580
01:07:59.829 --> 01:08:02.206
<i>suddenly Rhaenyra
understands that she was right.</i>

581
01:08:02.207 --> 01:08:05.834
that people with
some Targaryen blood

582
01:08:05.835 --> 01:08:08.046
<i>somewhere in their
lineage can claim dragons.</i>

583
01:08:09.172 --> 01:08:11.549
- These people are...
- Courageous.

584
01:08:12.550 --> 01:08:13.385
Mongrels.

585
01:08:13.551 --> 01:08:14.973
<i>Yeah. it's a big. big moment.</i>

586
01:08:15.053 --> 01:08:17.097
<i>You know. obviously.
last time that Jace</i>

587
01:08:17.222 --> 01:08:18.847
<i>probably would've said
anything was in season one.</i>

588
01:08:18.848 --> 01:08:21.726
when little Jace said.
"Am I a bastard?"

589
01:08:21.851 --> 01:08:23.728
House Targaryen is
the blood of the dragon.

590
01:08:23.895 --> 01:08:25.854
If any may lay claim
to it. what are we then?

591
01:08:25.855 --> 01:08:27.295
Jace very simply
looks at it as like.

592
01:08:27.399 --> 01:08:30.192
<i>"You're going to just take any
gutter rat from King's Landing</i>

593
01:08:30.193 --> 01:08:31.527
<i>and try to put them on dragons?</i>

594
01:08:31.528 --> 01:08:33.238
<i>It makes me a common aristocrat</i>

595
01:08:33.363 --> 01:08:35.240
<i>with black hair and
a checkered past."</i>

596
01:08:42.872 --> 01:08:43.873
My Lord.

597
01:08:44.082 --> 01:08:45.249
My Lord?

598
01:08:45.250 --> 01:08:46.918
How you have
come up in the world.

599
01:08:47.085 --> 01:08:48.544
<i>Being initially shocked.</i>

600
01:08:48.545 --> 01:08:50.088
<i>Corlys is then very proud.</i>

601
01:08:50.255 --> 01:08:51.547
<i>It's because that's my son.</i>

602
01:08:51.548 --> 01:08:53.549
Off his own back. he's
made something of himself.

603
01:08:53.550 --> 01:08:55.301
And I think that's very
important for Corlys

604
01:08:55.427 --> 01:08:57.262
because that's how
he sees himself.

605
01:08:59.431 --> 01:09:00.432
Well done.

606
01:09:01.099 --> 01:09:05.227
Yes. two words. but they
mean just more than "well done."

607
01:09:05.228 --> 01:09:07.272
They're... They
mean. "I see you."

608
01:09:09.816 --> 01:09:11.484
<i>Daemon goes
out into the godswood.</i>

609
01:09:11.609 --> 01:09:12.697
expecting a certain outcome.

610
01:09:12.777 --> 01:09:15.613
and then the fun of that
scene is seeing all the cards

611
01:09:15.739 --> 01:09:16.781
as they're turned over.

612
01:09:17.115 --> 01:09:20.242
Why should we now follow a
boy when you will align with one

613
01:09:20.243 --> 01:09:22.619
who will desecrate the
innocent to reach his aims?

614
01:09:22.620 --> 01:09:24.913
<i>Not only are you going
to have to show your belly to them</i>

615
01:09:24.914 --> 01:09:26.082
<i>in order to get your way...</i>

616
01:09:26.458 --> 01:09:29.126
I may have been a
touch enthusiastic

617
01:09:29.127 --> 01:09:30.420
in pursuing my aims.

618
01:09:30.628 --> 01:09:31.628
Seize him.

619
01:09:31.755 --> 01:09:34.007
Your Grace. command
them. I've only served you.

620
01:09:34.257 --> 01:09:36.012
But now you're going
to go one step further

621
01:09:36.092 --> 01:09:38.345
and actually take
the head of this guy

622
01:09:38.470 --> 01:09:41.305
that pledged his
life in service to you.

623
01:09:41.306 --> 01:09:42.307
No. no. no!

624
01:09:42.474 --> 01:09:44.229
Daemon isn't the most
honorable guy in the world.

625
01:09:44.309 --> 01:09:47.020
but I think he does have
that kind of mafia honor to him.

626
01:09:47.145 --> 01:09:48.980
<i>He's made this sort
of life-and-death pact</i>

627
01:09:49.105 --> 01:09:51.273
<i>with Willem Blackwood
and said. "You do my way.</i>

628
01:09:51.274 --> 01:09:53.193
<i>and I'll see that the
sky's the limit for you."</i>

629
01:09:53.318 --> 01:09:54.819
<i>He's so used to
being in control.</i>

630
01:09:54.944 --> 01:09:56.584
and it all just slips
through his fingers.

631
01:09:58.156 --> 01:10:00.992
<i>And you see how he just
comes apart at the end of it.</i>

632
01:10:04.996 --> 01:10:06.955
<i>I had a long
conversation with Paddy.</i>

633
01:10:06.956 --> 01:10:08.290
<i>and he said.
"I'll play the part.</i>

634
01:10:08.291 --> 01:10:10.626
but I want to play
the final scene.

635
01:10:10.627 --> 01:10:11.794
when he offers the crown up.

636
01:10:11.795 --> 01:10:13.838
I want to do it in the
decrepit makeup."

637
01:10:14.631 --> 01:10:17.175
It was Paddy's idea.
which is just a clever idea.

638
01:10:17.300 --> 01:10:20.177
And then he turns around.
and Daemon. for the first time.

639
01:10:20.178 --> 01:10:24.014
sees the full kind of
degradation of his face.

640
01:10:24.015 --> 01:10:25.474
<i>And he presents him the crown.</i>

641
01:10:25.475 --> 01:10:27.894
<i>He's like. "God. is that
what I wanted? Do I need it?"</i>

642
01:10:28.019 --> 01:10:29.646
There's a lot going
on in that scene.

643
01:10:29.979 --> 01:10:31.523
Do you want it still?

644
01:10:33.483 --> 01:10:34.817
<i>One of the things I love about</i>

645
01:10:34.818 --> 01:10:38.405
House of the Dragon <i>is that
it's a generational narrative.</i>

646
01:10:38.530 --> 01:10:40.699
We have a lot of
young characters

647
01:10:40.824 --> 01:10:44.244
that are all coming of age.
one of whom is Rhaena.

648
01:10:44.369 --> 01:10:46.537
<i>Lady
Jeyne's been promised a dragon.</i>

649
01:10:46.538 --> 01:10:49.331
<i>She receives two. but it's
like. asterisk. they're babies.</i>

650
01:10:49.332 --> 01:10:51.042
<i>They can't protect her.</i>

651
01:10:52.210 --> 01:10:53.836
<i>So. when she
embarks on her journey.</i>

652
01:10:53.837 --> 01:10:55.337
she's desperate to find. like.

653
01:10:55.338 --> 01:10:56.760
<i>more than just a
dragon. it's purpose.</i>

654
01:10:56.840 --> 01:10:59.384
<i>She doesn't stop. and
she's not going to stop.</i>

655
01:11:01.886 --> 01:11:05.223
<i>In episode
seven. Alicent has lost any power.</i>

656
01:11:05.348 --> 01:11:06.891
<i>any legitimacy that she held.</i>

657
01:11:07.017 --> 01:11:11.604
<i>She does notice a cut similar
in placement to Rhaenyra's.</i>

658
01:11:11.730 --> 01:11:14.566
and I think it sort
of brings into focus

659
01:11:14.691 --> 01:11:16.609
the absurdity of it all.

660
01:11:17.235 --> 01:11:19.070
I wish to go out. Ser Rickard.

661
01:11:19.195 --> 01:11:23.032
Her need to escape
King's Landing

662
01:11:23.033 --> 01:11:25.200
is to sort of zoom
out from it all a bit

663
01:11:25.201 --> 01:11:27.870
and get some clarity
on the situation.

664
01:11:27.871 --> 01:11:29.247
<i>Alicent's disillusioned.</i>

665
01:11:29.372 --> 01:11:31.248
She doesn't know that she
has a place in the Red Keep.

666
01:11:31.249 --> 01:11:33.084
or if she did.
whether she wants it.

667
01:11:33.418 --> 01:11:35.465
<i>And I think at the beginning
of it. we're sort of wondering.</i>

668
01:11:35.545 --> 01:11:37.713
<i>"Is Alicent out
here to end it all?"</i>

669
01:11:37.714 --> 01:11:42.051
This moment of peace
that could potentially be

670
01:11:42.052 --> 01:11:43.428
the last time for her.

671
01:11:43.595 --> 01:11:46.097
<i>We see her go
through a bit of an awakening.</i>

672
01:11:46.264 --> 01:11:47.264
<i>When her eyes open.</i>

673
01:11:47.432 --> 01:11:49.476
snap back into reality
with a sense of purpose.

674
01:11:49.601 --> 01:11:52.103
I mean. what that purpose
is remains to be seen.

675
01:11:59.444 --> 01:12:01.821
<i>The dragonkeepers
very much reject Rhaenyra's idea.</i>

676
01:12:01.946 --> 01:12:03.114
<i>so Rhaenyra is left alone.</i>

677
01:12:03.239 --> 01:12:05.074
<i>This was actually Emma's
pitch for Rhaenyra to go</i>

678
01:12:05.075 --> 01:12:06.909
<i>and. like. walk
amongst the seeds.</i>

679
01:12:06.910 --> 01:12:09.411
<i>as though a pastor
amongst her flock</i>

680
01:12:09.412 --> 01:12:11.246
in the terms of
a religious cult.

681
01:12:11.247 --> 01:12:13.583
Suffering will be ended.

682
01:12:13.750 --> 01:12:15.835
And without bloodshed.

683
01:12:21.299 --> 01:12:23.425
<i>When you realize
that Rhaenyra is just basically</i>

684
01:12:23.426 --> 01:12:26.304
<i>throwing stuff against the
wall and seeing whether it sticks</i>

685
01:12:26.429 --> 01:12:28.306
<i>and seeing if somebody
can emerge from this.</i>

686
01:12:28.473 --> 01:12:29.808
<i>it goes very bad. very quickly.</i>

687
01:12:29.974 --> 01:12:32.519
In many ways. I think there's
a way of looking at that scene

688
01:12:32.644 --> 01:12:34.436
as ritual sacrifice.

689
01:12:38.817 --> 01:12:40.196
<i>The whole
sequence where I'm running</i>

690
01:12:40.276 --> 01:12:41.944
<i>through the cavern
in front of Vermithor.</i>

691
01:12:41.945 --> 01:12:44.030
it took a whole
day of rehearsing.

692
01:12:44.155 --> 01:12:45.657
running it through
with the Steadicam.

693
01:12:47.659 --> 01:12:49.494
<i>They call Vermithor
the Bronze Fury.</i>

694
01:12:49.619 --> 01:12:51.705
<i>and I think that's
really fitting for Hugh.</i>

695
01:12:51.830 --> 01:12:53.498
He's quite angry inside.

696
01:12:53.623 --> 01:12:57.002
Come on!

697
01:12:57.210 --> 01:12:58.210
<i>It's a mystery.</i>

698
01:12:58.378 --> 01:13:00.295
<i>No one really knows
how the Targaryens</i>

699
01:13:00.296 --> 01:13:02.298
are talking to the dragons.

700
01:13:03.883 --> 01:13:06.363
<i>We wanted to not just
see the same thing again and again.</i>

701
01:13:06.469 --> 01:13:09.029
which is a guy claiming a dragon
and getting it to bend the neck.

702
01:13:13.560 --> 01:13:16.479
Every fiber of Ulf's
body wants out.

703
01:13:17.731 --> 01:13:20.191
<i>Close my eyes.
pray for a quick death.</i>

704
01:13:20.859 --> 01:13:21.901
which doesn't come.

705
01:13:22.027 --> 01:13:23.227
I think it's that supplication

706
01:13:23.319 --> 01:13:25.696
and the way that he showed
deference to Silverwing

707
01:13:25.697 --> 01:13:27.574
<i>that probably makes
her choose him.</i>

708
01:13:27.699 --> 01:13:30.034
But we didn't want to get too
much into the whys and hows.

709
01:13:30.035 --> 01:13:32.871
We don't really understand
why a dragon chooses its rider.

710
01:13:33.038 --> 01:13:36.666
I've said I'm a Targaryen.
Turns out. I'm a Targaryen.

711
01:13:37.709 --> 01:13:39.252
<i>Dragon!</i>

712
01:13:40.712 --> 01:13:43.172
<i>I don't think the news of
Seasmoke really reached Aemond.</i>

713
01:13:43.173 --> 01:13:44.548
<i>and you can tell that by the way</i>

714
01:13:44.549 --> 01:13:46.675
<i>Larys and Ironrod
exchanged glances</i>

715
01:13:46.676 --> 01:13:48.553
when they hear the
dragon flying over the city

716
01:13:48.720 --> 01:13:50.800
because I think they both
assumed that it's Seasmoke.

717
01:13:50.930 --> 01:13:53.892
<i>Rhaenyra's
raised new riders in the dragonseeds.</i>

718
01:13:54.059 --> 01:13:56.018
Aemond retaliates
without even thinking.

719
01:13:56.019 --> 01:13:57.103
and he goes to meet them.

720
01:13:57.228 --> 01:13:58.396
Open the gates!

721
01:13:58.563 --> 01:14:00.440
<i>He was supposed
to be the special one.</i>

722
01:14:00.565 --> 01:14:02.320
<i>The fact that somebody
else is out there that did this</i>

723
01:14:02.400 --> 01:14:03.443
<i>just breaks his brain.</i>

724
01:14:03.568 --> 01:14:05.115
<i>So. his immediate
response is. of course.</i>

725
01:14:05.195 --> 01:14:07.450
<i>he rides and gets on his
dragon with the intent of going out</i>

726
01:14:07.530 --> 01:14:08.739
<i>and killing Silverwing.</i>

727
01:14:08.740 --> 01:14:10.742
And he gets more
than he bargained for.

728
01:14:13.703 --> 01:14:16.081
<i>And for the first time
since season one.</i>

729
01:14:16.247 --> 01:14:17.749
<i>we see fear in his eye.</i>

730
01:14:19.793 --> 01:14:22.586
<i>And literally. the Dragon Queen
coming out of the Dragonmont.</i>

731
01:14:22.587 --> 01:14:25.465
<i>Not only Silverwing.
but Vermithor and also Syrax.</i>

732
01:14:25.590 --> 01:14:27.716
And whatever questions
she was faced with.

733
01:14:27.717 --> 01:14:28.759
she was right in the end

734
01:14:28.760 --> 01:14:31.262
and was able to assemble
this army of dragons.

735
